      "patch": "@@ -0,0 +1,5 @@\n+created: 2025-12-30\n+title: Configurable Metadata Detection\n+intro: >-\n+  This release adds configuration options to disable automatic PR and author detection,\n+  giving projects more control over changelog entry metadata."
    },
    {
      "sha": "b0c5203d13e6a4972adccef3f9b52bfe7aefca5d",
      "filename": "changelog/releases/v0.19.0/notes.md",
      "status": "added",
      "additions": 9,
      "deletions": 0,
      "changes": 9,
      "blob_url": "https://github.com/tenzir/ship/blob/43a43d72daf0689a20a773401b3a1457aa667d1f/changelog%2Freleases%2Fv0.19.0%2Fnotes.md",
      "raw_url": "https://github.com/tenzir/ship/raw/43a43d72daf0689a20a773401b3a1457aa667d1f/changelog%2Freleases%2Fv0.19.0%2Fnotes.md",
      "contents_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/tenzir/ship/contents/changelog%2Freleases%2Fv0.19.0%2Fnotes.md?ref=43a43d72daf0689a20a773401b3a1457aa667d1f",
      "patch": "@@ -0,0 +1,9 @@\n+This release adds configuration options to disable automatic PR and author detection, giving projects more control over changelog entry metadata.\n+\n+## \ud83d\ude80 Features\n+\n+### Disable automatic PR and author detection\n+\n+Add `omit_pr` and `omit_author` configuration options to prevent automatic inference of PR numbers and authors. When these config options are set to `true`, the `add` command will not auto-detect PR numbers from git branches or infer authors from git commits. If users explicitly provide `--pr` or `--author` flags while the corresponding omit option is enabled, a warning message is emitted and the value is ignored. This gives projects fine-grained control over changelog entry metadata.\n+\n+*By @mavam and @claude.*"
    },
